   <concept id="FAR_19_1303">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">19.1303</ph> Status as a HUBZone small business concern.</title>
      <conbody>
         <ol id="d1232e13">
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            Status as a HUBZone small business concern is determined by the Small Business Administration (SBA) in accordance with <ph outputclass="CFR">13 CFR Part 126</ph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2022-08 October 28, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-007?>If SBA determines that a concern is a HUBZone small business, it will designate the concern as a HUBZone small business in the Dynamic Small Business Search (DSBS) at <i>
                        <xref href="https://web.sba.gov/pro-net/search/dsp_dsbs.cfm"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">https://web.sba.gov/​pro-net/​search/​dsp_​dsbs.cfm</xref>.</i> SBA's designation also appears in SAM. Only firms designated in DSBS and SAM as HUBZone small business concerns are eligible for HUBZone preferences. HUBZone preferences are not contingent on the place of performance.<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.1303 by revising paragraphs (b)?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e29">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2022-08 October 28, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2017-019?>A joint venture may be considered a HUBZone small business concern if—<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.1303 by revising paragraph (c).?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol rev="FAC 2022-08 October 28, 2022">
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e38">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>The joint venture qualifies as small under <xref href="19.301-1.dita#FAR_19_301_1" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">19.301-1</xref>(a)(2)(i);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e46">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>At least one party to the joint venture is a HUBZone small business concern; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e51">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>The joint venture complies with <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-13/section-126.616#p-126.616(a)"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">13 CFR 126.616(a)</xref> through <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-13/section-126.616#p-126.616(c)"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">(c)</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1266e34">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2022-08 October 28, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-007?>To be eligible for a HUBZone contract under this section, a HUBZone small business concern must be a HUBZone small business concern at the time of its initial offer.<?FM MARKER [Why] and (d)?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p> </p>
      </conbody>
